						               													<description>Light-strategy tabletop card game. Each player takes the role of a mountain Llama Farmer trying to make the most money ('Bucks') selling llama-wool rugs.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players start with their own small herd of randomised primary coloured llama cards. Each turn players expand, shear, weave or sell.&amp;#10;Expanding adds new primary coloured llamas, or expands the llama 'family-tree' making more complex colours and patterns available.&amp;#10;Shearing produces wool, either unpredictably with a repeatable 'light shear' based on selected dice and numbers on the llama cards producing wool for any farmer or a one-shot 'close shave' which guarantees wool at the cost of a chilly looking llama!&amp;#10;Weaving combines wools into new colours or rugs and selling trades rugs for bucks in the markets. High-fashion markets want specific rugs and pay well, but a general market will buy any rug cheaply.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game ends when all the high-fashion markets close, and the farmer with the most bucks wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Strategy choice comes from choosing the right rugs and llamas to go for, balancing expanding and shearing and knowing when to apply a close shave.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
